msItem.title: Genesis
msItem.incipit: Jn deme anbeginne alder dynghe schop got den hemmel vnde erden
msItem.explicit: Vt sineme slechte wart geboren Saul de ersste koningh der Joden vnd Jesse vnd damit ok Salamon
msItem.note: The beginning (ff. 2r-7r) is taken from the Sächsische Weltchronik (Saxon World Chronicle; Derendorf 1996: 172).

msItem.title: Exodus
msItem.incipit: Men lesst vortmer in den boken in Exodij dat heth

foliation.p: Traces of a contemporary folation in roman numerals in the first quire.

layout.p: Written in two columns. Rubrics and initials in red.

handNote.p: Possibly written by different hands. Finished 1482 by Jens Nielsen from Aalborg.

decoNote.p: On the verso of fol. 1 (flyleaf) a red pen-drawn lion is found.

additions.p: On the flyleaf the number 471 was added in red chalk; it is probably a number from the auction catalogue.
On the originally blank fol. 138r, some Latin sayings with translations into Old Danish were written down.
